In this structure, `CommonEventBase` serves as the common foundation for all specific event types that share the same parameters and methods, with `uniqueAction()` being an example of a method that each derived class must implement uniquely.

### Conclusion

Adopting this inheritance-based model, you achieve a design that’s scalable, easy to maintain, and adherent to sound object-oriented principles. It reflects a thoughtful approach to design in your event management system, accommodating shared functionality elegantly while preserving the specialized behaviors of individual event types.

